To figure out if your computer has 64 bit or 32 bit processor :  
uname -a
lscpu (look at the architecture row)

// After getting the tar file from Oracle website and un-archiving it, we need to update the PATH variable.
// Go to the home directory : cd ~

(This will install openjdk as opposed to Oracle JDK)
sudo apt-get install default-jdk
sudo apt-get install default-jre


